"If you only care about the pdf and cdf you can use the gamma approximation which will be exact when integers and a continuos interpolation in-between. It is what is used in RooFit.\n\nthanks @pablodecm -- I was looking at that approx as well. Do you have a efficient numpy implementation of it by any chance?\n\nThis should work, if you do not mind the scipy dependency (I believe you are already using it).\r\n\r\n````python\r\nimport numpy as np\r\nfrom scipy.special import gammaln\r\n\r\ndef poisson_pdf(k, r):\r\n    \"\"\" k is are the counts are r is the rate \"\"\"\r\n    return np.exp(k*np.log(r)-r-gammaln(k+1.))\r\n````\r\n"